data.description: *SPECIAL SELLER CREDIT TO ANY BUYERS NOT WORKING WITH AN AGENT! YOU CAN SAVE BIG! Welcome Home to this gorgeous home in the highly desirable Stone Haven Subdivision. Built-in 2019, this 5 bedroom, 4 bathroom, and 3-car garage home offers today’s desirable features of grand interior and outdoor living spaces, with direct access to walking trails and parks nearby. From the home’s rocking chair front porch enter into the foyer that is flanked by an office with French doors, and a formal dining room highlighted with a modern chandelier. Continue into the fireside great room that is open to the kitchen and the informal dining area. The kitchen is defined by beautiful white cabinetry, a subway-tiled backsplashes, stainless steel appliances, including a new gas range, a walk-in pantry, and a large island with a granite countertop. Walk out to the private outdoor living space that features a fenced backyard, and a covered patio complete with a sitting area by the fireplace. You'll love the in-law suite on the main level. Retreat upstairs to an expansive owner’s suite with a luxurious bathroom with an upgraded frameless shower, double vanities and a huge customized walk-in closet! The upper level also includes three additional guest bedrooms and two bathrooms, a large laundry room, and a media room or library. The home offers immense street appeal with manicured front yard and a private backyard bordered by a new fence. Stone Haven’s amenities include a fully loaded gym, pool, tennis courts, a playground, and a clubhouse. In addition, the community has direct access to the Harris Greenway Trail as well as to the Tribble Mill Park and the Harbins Park.
